Sentencas: Ni-YSZ cermet anodes for solid oxide fuel cells were successfully prepared by high frequency induction heated sintering, producing a uniformly porous microstructure without abnormal grain growth found in the conventional sintering method.
Titulo: Preparation of porous Ni-YSZ cermet anodes for solid oxide fuel cells by high frequency induction heated sintering

Sentencas: All sintering processes commenced below 1150 degrees C and finished within 2 min.
Titulo: Preparation of porous Ni-YSZ cermet anodes for solid oxide fuel cells by high frequency induction heated sintering

Sentencas: The rupture strength and electrical conductivity of the sample sintered by high frequency induction heated sintering without addition of a pore former were over 180 MPa and about 2000 S cm(-1) at 800 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Preparation of porous Ni-YSZ cermet anodes for solid oxide fuel cells by high frequency induction heated sintering
